The hunt for the killers of two metro police officers in Durban intensifies as the Organised Crime Unit gets involved. Courtesy of #DSTV403 DURBAN - The hunt for the killers of two metro police officers in Durban intensified as the Organised Crime Unit got involved. The officers were on protection duty when they were gunned down on Monday night. Durban ward councillor Moses Zulu said he's previously received death threats. READ: Durban councillor scared after police officers shot dead outside home The eThekwini Municipality is calling for any information that'll help catch the killers.
Constable Sonto Mhlanga died at the roadside, while Inspector F Dladla's body was found in his vehicle. Their firearms were taken.